WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:09.200
[insects trilling]

00:18.000 --> 00:21.360
[muttering]

00:21.400 --> 00:23.560
Un, deux, trois,

00:23.600 --> 00:26.040
quatre...

00:29.720 --> 00:32.120
[sighs]

00:37.200 --> 00:39.000
-[mutters]
-Gloria.

00:40.240 --> 00:41.880
I'm joining you today.

00:41.920 --> 00:44.600
The boss didn't say
anything about...

00:44.640 --> 00:46.120
Last minute change.

00:47.600 --> 00:48.560
Where's the rest?

00:48.600 --> 00:51.080
It's not loaded yet.

00:51.120 --> 00:53.560
What's inside?

00:53.600 --> 00:56.440
Does it matter?

01:04.880 --> 01:06.320
Let's get the rest loaded.

01:06.360 --> 01:07.640
Oui.

01:07.680 --> 01:09.680
♪ ♪

01:16.680 --> 01:18.640
EMMANUEL:
You think your husband

01:18.680 --> 01:21.080
-sent you this?
-GEORGIA: I don't know.

01:21.120 --> 01:23.120
Why, after all this time,
why would he--

01:23.160 --> 01:25.520
-So, how does Pieter Bello
fit in?
-Pie-- Sorry, Pieter who?

01:25.560 --> 01:28.240
There was a man with Will on
that news footage holding a gun.

01:28.280 --> 01:30.560
Pieter Bello. Ex-military.
What are you doing?

01:30.600 --> 01:33.440
I know what I'm not doing.
I'm not just going home.

01:33.480 --> 01:35.440
Not now.

01:35.480 --> 01:38.200
How far is this from here?

01:40.240 --> 01:42.120
[indistinct chatter]

01:42.160 --> 01:44.280
GEORGIA: So you're telling me
someone can send me a car

01:44.320 --> 01:46.800
and you have no record, none,
of who paid for it,

01:46.840 --> 01:49.400
who's responsible for it,
how it's insured, nothing.

01:49.440 --> 01:50.800
Parlez lentement,
s'il vous plaît, Madame.

01:50.840 --> 01:51.880
Je ne comprends pas.

01:51.920 --> 01:53.760
-[sighs]
-[speaking French]

01:58.560 --> 02:01.080
What? What?

02:01.120 --> 02:03.080
He says a-a man came.
A white man.

02:03.120 --> 02:05.320
He was paid
to keep it off the system.

02:05.360 --> 02:07.600
-No record was kept.
-Okay. What did he look like?

02:08.440 --> 02:10.800
Was it either of these men?

02:10.840 --> 02:13.280
[speaking French]

02:14.880 --> 02:17.880
[sighs, mutters]

02:20.160 --> 02:22.600
[indistinct chatter]

02:35.800 --> 02:37.800
♪ ♪

02:47.600 --> 02:50.000
I'm sorry about back there.
I just...

02:50.040 --> 02:53.440
I just keep wondering, what
if Will did leave that note?

02:53.480 --> 02:55.080
What if he doesn't want
to be found?

02:55.120 --> 02:58.320
If that was so, would you
turn around and walk away?

02:58.360 --> 03:00.000
Probably not.

03:00.040 --> 03:02.600
I looked online.

03:02.640 --> 03:06.040
Pieter Bello was an officer
in the South African Infantry.

03:06.080 --> 03:08.440
I cannot see when he left,
but he started a company here,

03:08.480 --> 03:10.480
in Kinshasa, five years ago.

03:10.520 --> 03:12.920
-Bulletscreen Security.
-Was there an address listed?

03:12.960 --> 03:15.480
Yes, but the company folded.

03:15.520 --> 03:17.480
That doesn't matter.
That's something, isn't it?

03:17.520 --> 03:19.920
Yes. That it is.

03:22.600 --> 03:24.840
Let's go.

03:24.880 --> 03:27.240
[birds calling]

03:27.280 --> 03:29.680
[bicycle bell rings]

03:34.880 --> 03:37.280
[beeping, buzzing]

03:43.400 --> 03:45.160
[trash can opens]

03:45.200 --> 03:46.360
[soft thud]

03:52.600 --> 03:53.960
BEATRIX:
Hey.

03:54.000 --> 03:56.280
ARIEL:
Hey. Hey.

03:59.640 --> 04:01.600
[sighs]

04:01.640 --> 04:03.600
So...

04:06.040 --> 04:09.000
-So... [chuckles]
-[chuckles]

04:09.040 --> 04:14.080
Tell me about the plane crash.

04:14.120 --> 04:17.720
Um, I'm-I'm not ready
to talk about it.

04:17.760 --> 04:19.880
Sorry.
[clears throat]

04:19.920 --> 04:21.120
No, I'm sorry.

04:21.160 --> 04:24.080
So, after the operation,

04:24.120 --> 04:26.600
what's the first painting
I should see?

04:26.640 --> 04:28.320
[inhales sharply, grunts]

04:28.360 --> 04:30.400
You know,

04:30.440 --> 04:33.600
I'm no connoisseur, but, um,

04:33.640 --> 04:36.520
I did go
to the Musée d'Orsay once,

04:36.560 --> 04:38.720
just to kill time,

04:38.760 --> 04:41.640
-and I saw Whistler's Mother.
-[chuckles softly]

04:41.680 --> 04:43.680
Just...

04:43.720 --> 04:46.920
stopped me in my tracks
for some reason.

04:51.480 --> 04:53.440
Listen, this is--

04:53.480 --> 04:56.360
this isn't something that I...

04:56.400 --> 04:59.000
do very often.
Or ever, actually.

04:59.040 --> 05:00.760
Mm, strange.

05:00.800 --> 05:02.200
Uh, I do this...

05:02.240 --> 05:03.840
all the time.

05:03.880 --> 05:05.240
[chuckles]

05:05.280 --> 05:07.440
I, uh...

05:07.480 --> 05:09.040
I have to go to work.

05:09.080 --> 05:10.520
Right.

05:10.560 --> 05:12.080
Of course. Uh...

05:12.120 --> 05:13.880
You tune pianos, you said?

05:13.920 --> 05:17.480
Well, I'd rather be playing,
but, yeah, second best thing.

05:17.520 --> 05:19.280
-I sh-- I should go.
-[laughs] I don't have to go

05:19.320 --> 05:20.320
for an hour. You could--

05:20.360 --> 05:23.200
you could maybe have a shower.

05:23.240 --> 05:25.200
Could shower.

05:25.240 --> 05:26.560
Mm-hmm.

05:26.600 --> 05:29.800
Or we could, um...

05:29.840 --> 05:31.040
[chuckles]

05:31.080 --> 05:33.480
Mmm. Ooh. Ah, ah!

05:33.520 --> 05:35.720
-[groans] I'm so sorry.
-It's okay.

05:35.760 --> 05:36.720
It's okay. Don't worry.

05:36.760 --> 05:38.520
-I'm so clumsy.
-Okay.

05:38.560 --> 05:39.880
Doesn't matter.

05:39.920 --> 05:42.080
-[whispers]: Don't worry.
-Ah.

05:42.120 --> 05:44.160
Oh, I'm covered in, uh,

05:44.200 --> 05:46.160
-tea.
-That's the way I like it.

05:46.200 --> 05:49.560
-Ooh. [chuckles]
-[chuckles]

05:49.600 --> 05:51.480
[horns honking]

05:51.520 --> 05:53.440
[indistinct chatter]

05:53.480 --> 05:55.680
So, come on, what
really happened to your car?

05:55.720 --> 05:58.080
It looks like you drove it
through a war zone.

05:58.120 --> 06:00.800
Like I said, some people have
an unfortunate way

06:00.840 --> 06:02.920
-of expressing their anger.
-That's not an answer.

06:02.960 --> 06:04.960
It is my answer.

06:08.240 --> 06:10.520
What number is, uh,
Bulletscreen Security?

06:10.560 --> 06:12.760
It doesn't say.
Just this building.

06:12.800 --> 06:15.760
191 Boulevard du 30 Juin.

06:15.800 --> 06:18.200
Hey.

06:28.160 --> 06:30.320
What are you looking for?

06:42.680 --> 06:45.600
-[clears throat]
Georgia, you need to stop now.
-Yeah, just a minute.

06:45.640 --> 06:47.640
[whispers]:
I mean now.

06:49.920 --> 06:51.960
[door shuts]

06:54.760 --> 06:57.520
EMMANUEL [quietly]:
Wait, what was that?

06:57.560 --> 06:59.520
You could have got us
into trouble.

06:59.560 --> 07:01.120
Did you find something,
at least?

07:01.160 --> 07:02.760
I hope so.

07:02.800 --> 07:05.360
It's a letter addressed
to Bulletscreen Security

07:05.400 --> 07:06.560
dated a few days ago.

07:06.600 --> 07:07.960
Maybe they don't know
his office closed.

07:10.760 --> 07:13.240
It's an insurance company.

07:13.280 --> 07:14.640
Two policyholders
are mentioned.

07:14.680 --> 07:16.480
Pieter Bello and Vanda Steyn.

07:16.520 --> 07:18.320
Look, there's an address.

07:21.800 --> 07:24.200
[horns honking]

07:24.240 --> 07:27.080
[indistinct chatter]

07:44.200 --> 07:46.600
[doorbell rings]

07:48.720 --> 07:51.680
GEORGIA:
Are you Vanda Steyn?

07:53.160 --> 07:54.680
Do you know Pieter Bello?

07:56.320 --> 07:57.680
Sure.

07:57.720 --> 08:00.760
I was married to the bastard
for 15 years.

08:00.800 --> 08:03.200
[coughing]

08:08.800 --> 08:10.800
[lighter clicks]

08:11.800 --> 08:13.720
So, what is it you want to know?

08:13.760 --> 08:16.400
We're trying to find
your ex-husband.

08:17.400 --> 08:19.320
Who are you anyway, huh?

08:19.360 --> 08:21.760
What do you want with him?

08:22.920 --> 08:24.680
Three years ago,

08:24.720 --> 08:27.120
my husband died
in Sankuru Airways Flight 19.

08:27.160 --> 08:28.160
But then...

08:29.640 --> 08:31.880
...I saw him, in Kinshasa,

08:31.920 --> 08:33.520
just a few days ago.

08:33.560 --> 08:35.200
That is your ex, isn't it?

08:36.760 --> 08:38.480
Ja.

08:40.480 --> 08:43.120
So, if this man of yours
was in a plane crash,

08:43.160 --> 08:44.640
what's he doing
walking around town?

08:44.680 --> 08:46.960
That's what I want
to talk to your ex about.

08:48.000 --> 08:49.880
I don't know where he is, okay?

08:49.920 --> 08:52.240
And I don't care. And
the further anyone stays away

08:52.280 --> 08:53.600
from that doos,the better.

08:53.640 --> 08:55.000
He's the reason I'm even here.

08:55.040 --> 08:56.480
Got thrown out of the army.

08:56.520 --> 08:58.680
Promised me everything
is gonna be better.

08:58.720 --> 09:00.240
Here, of all places.

09:00.280 --> 09:02.440
And what
about his security business?

09:02.480 --> 09:04.040
Why did it close?

09:04.080 --> 09:07.240
Well, things started going
a bit south after the diagnosis.

09:07.280 --> 09:10.600
HIV he got from a street hooker
in Matonge.

09:10.640 --> 09:14.320
Kind enough to pass it on to me.

09:15.760 --> 09:18.280
Is there any way
we can get in touch with Pieter?

09:18.320 --> 09:20.840
Ja.Find a bar or a whorehouse.

09:20.880 --> 09:22.840
I don't talk-- Oh, shit.

09:22.880 --> 09:24.240
-Sorry.
-Don't worry.

09:24.280 --> 09:26.880
There's a bathroom
down the hall.

09:51.880 --> 09:54.280
[door creaks softly]

10:09.320 --> 10:11.160
We've taken up enough
of your time.

10:11.200 --> 10:13.520
EMMANUEL:
Uh, perhaps there is some way

10:13.560 --> 10:15.280
of getting a message
to your ex-husband.

10:15.320 --> 10:17.160
VANDA:
Hey. I told you,

10:17.200 --> 10:18.600
I don't talk to him.

10:18.640 --> 10:21.040
GEORGIA:
Thank you for your help.

10:23.000 --> 10:25.600
-She's lying through her teeth.
-How do you know?

10:25.640 --> 10:27.160
I went into her daughter's
bedroom. There were a bunch

10:27.200 --> 10:28.680
of birthday cards.
And this one

10:28.720 --> 10:30.640
was signed, "Love, Dad."

10:31.720 --> 10:32.920
[exhales]

10:32.960 --> 10:34.520
If you are right, if that woman

10:34.560 --> 10:36.280
knows where to find
Pieter Bello,

10:36.320 --> 10:37.840
-what can we do?
-What time

10:37.880 --> 10:39.880
do schools finish round here?

10:42.400 --> 10:44.440
[barge horn blowing]

10:46.720 --> 10:48.240
[chuckles, sniffles]

10:48.280 --> 10:50.720
I don't really want to go.

10:50.760 --> 10:51.960
Mm.

10:52.000 --> 10:53.840
-I'll see you soon.
-Yes.

10:53.880 --> 10:55.920
-DRIVER: Your taxi's here.
-See you soon.

10:55.960 --> 10:59.120
-Bye.
-Bye.

11:09.160 --> 11:10.120
[beeps]

11:10.160 --> 11:11.520
-Assist.
-[door shuts]

11:11.560 --> 11:14.320
-Search "plane crash Congo
2015."
-[engine starts]

11:15.360 --> 11:18.200
COMPUTER VOICE:
Sankuru Airways Flight 19

11:18.240 --> 11:23.040
was a Boeing 737 aircraft
that crashed in April 2015

11:23.080 --> 11:26.040
in the rainforest
in the Northern Kivu Province

11:26.080 --> 11:28.440
of the Democratic Republic
of Congo.

11:28.480 --> 11:31.600
The official report in 2016
attributed the accident

11:31.640 --> 11:34.640
to severe hydraulic failure.

11:34.680 --> 11:38.280
There were 86 fatalities,
including crew,

11:38.320 --> 11:42.640
and just one survivor, a nurse
called Dominique Mutombo,

11:42.680 --> 11:44.520
whose injuries were...

11:44.560 --> 11:46.280
[rewinds audio]

11:46.320 --> 11:50.880
...just one survivor, a nurse
called Dominique Mutombo...

11:50.920 --> 11:52.120
[phone beeps]

12:20.600 --> 12:24.240
Gaelle, I'm sorry.

12:28.800 --> 12:30.480
My love...

12:35.760 --> 12:38.120
How much money
do you owe them this time?

12:39.920 --> 12:42.720
You are a reckless idiot,
Emmanuel.

12:47.120 --> 12:50.480
But somehow you seem
to be my idiot.

12:53.440 --> 12:55.720
We need money.

12:59.400 --> 13:01.560
What are we going to do?

13:13.280 --> 13:15.720
GEORGIA [sighs]:
Oh, it's exhausting.

13:15.760 --> 13:18.800
-What?
-The possibilities
of what's going on.

13:18.840 --> 13:20.800
I'm just trying to choose
one version of events.

13:20.840 --> 13:22.920
Paralyzing.

13:22.960 --> 13:25.560
You know, my wife Ivette,

13:25.600 --> 13:29.200
she was online looking
for a toilet brush.

13:29.240 --> 13:31.840
There were 1,751

13:31.880 --> 13:33.720
different types available.

13:33.760 --> 13:36.320
Go on, then,
which one did she choose?

13:36.360 --> 13:38.800
She's still looking.

13:38.840 --> 13:40.360
[laughs]

13:44.480 --> 13:47.200
Thank you, Joseph.
I appreciate you coming.

13:49.680 --> 13:52.240
-Was that the chief of police?
-Yes, yes, it was.

13:52.280 --> 13:54.160
I thought I'd have
a word with him.

13:54.200 --> 13:56.640
About Will.

13:56.680 --> 13:59.360
Um, I'm not sure I follow.

13:59.400 --> 14:02.880
What's the point of having
contacts if you don't use them?

14:02.920 --> 14:04.880
Georgia doesn't think
anyone will listen to her,

14:04.920 --> 14:08.680
so I just thought
I'd ask Joseph to...

14:08.720 --> 14:10.680
-look into it.
-Look into what,

14:10.720 --> 14:12.680
Will coming back from the dead?

14:12.720 --> 14:16.480
I know. But if it was him in
the background at those riots,

14:16.520 --> 14:19.120
then maybe Joseph
can help find out.

14:19.160 --> 14:20.480
[sighs]:
Look...

14:20.520 --> 14:23.240
I just wanted to ask, okay?

14:23.280 --> 14:24.480
Okay.

14:24.520 --> 14:26.160
-Hey, Josh.
-Hmm?

14:26.200 --> 14:29.000
You're a sane, rational
human being, aren't you?

14:29.040 --> 14:31.000
Feel like this is
a trick question.

14:31.040 --> 14:33.600
-Proving your sanity.
-Glad I passed the test.

14:33.640 --> 14:35.760
Well, let's not get
ahead of ourselves.

14:35.800 --> 14:37.280
I mean....

14:37.320 --> 14:40.400
what do you think
about all of this?

14:40.440 --> 14:42.960
I don't know.

14:43.000 --> 14:46.520
Be really nice to see him again,
wouldn't it?

14:46.560 --> 14:48.360
Yeah, it would.

14:52.080 --> 14:54.880
-He has my 50 quid.
-[laughs]

14:55.880 --> 14:57.680
[sighs]

14:57.720 --> 14:59.520
[laughs]

15:03.480 --> 15:07.160
I don't think
we can simply walk inside.

15:07.200 --> 15:10.160
So we'll just wait
till they finish.

15:12.560 --> 15:14.520
I'm sorry, I didn't mean to...

15:14.560 --> 15:17.120
It's fine.
It happened a long time ago.

15:17.160 --> 15:18.720
Before the crash.
After...

15:18.760 --> 15:20.880
I-I understand.

15:22.240 --> 15:24.440
Well, I'm glad someone does.

15:24.480 --> 15:26.600
Feels like it happened
to someone else.

15:26.640 --> 15:28.960
Well, I am glad

15:29.000 --> 15:31.640
you did not succeed
in your efforts.

15:31.680 --> 15:34.720
Look, you don't have
to be here for all this.

15:34.760 --> 15:36.560
You know? It's myproblem,

15:36.600 --> 15:38.520
not yours.

15:38.560 --> 15:39.800
I do.

15:39.840 --> 15:41.440
I owe it to Gaelle.

15:41.480 --> 15:44.240
-[phone ringing]
-You see, she... Oh.

15:44.280 --> 15:46.080
-Excuse me.
-Sure.

15:46.120 --> 15:48.200
[speaks French]

15:48.240 --> 15:51.040
Okay. Don't move.
I'll be right over.

15:51.080 --> 15:52.320
Yes, of course.

15:52.360 --> 15:54.600
-I am sorry, I need to get home.
-Is everything okay?

15:54.640 --> 15:56.280
It will be.

15:56.320 --> 15:58.480
I'll stay here. You go.

15:58.520 --> 16:00.840
-Sorry.
-I'll be fine.

16:00.880 --> 16:03.520
Just... go.

16:03.560 --> 16:05.280
[starts engine]

16:07.960 --> 16:09.960
[tires squeal]

16:12.720 --> 16:14.720
[indistinct chatter, shouting]

16:31.960 --> 16:34.480
[exhales]

16:34.520 --> 16:37.080
♪ ♪

16:39.680 --> 16:41.720
[school bell ringing]

16:55.240 --> 16:56.840
Mia Bello?

16:56.880 --> 16:58.760
I'm a friend of your dad's.

16:58.800 --> 17:01.480
He's had an accident, Mia.

17:01.520 --> 17:03.520
You need to come with me.

17:05.360 --> 17:07.360
[TV droning in foreign language]

17:15.520 --> 17:17.520
[telephone ringing]

17:18.960 --> 17:21.280
-What?
-MAN [on speaker]:
Is this Vanda Steyn?

17:21.320 --> 17:22.920
Yeah.

17:22.960 --> 17:25.240
MAN: I'm calling
from Akram Hospital.

17:25.280 --> 17:27.160
-Your daughter Mia...
-Mia?

17:27.200 --> 17:29.000
...she has been in an accident.

17:29.040 --> 17:31.040
Yes, yes, I'm...
I'm on my way.

17:34.160 --> 17:36.480
Come on!

17:50.720 --> 17:53.320
[tires screeching]

17:54.960 --> 17:57.480
Move. Move!

17:57.520 --> 18:00.320
[speaks indistinctly]

18:00.360 --> 18:03.000
-I'm looking for Mia Bello.
-There's a queue, lady!

18:03.040 --> 18:05.520
-I can see that, you fool!
My daughter...
-Mum?

18:07.120 --> 18:09.760
VANDA:
I thought you...

18:09.800 --> 18:11.560
Oh, I thought you were...

18:11.600 --> 18:13.240
MIA:
Can I see Dad now?

18:13.280 --> 18:15.000
What?

18:19.720 --> 18:20.960
VANDA:
You arranged this?

18:21.000 --> 18:22.520
MIA:
I don't understand.

18:22.560 --> 18:24.000
VANDA:
Baby, Daddy's not here.

18:24.040 --> 18:25.760
-She said...
-She's right, Mia.

18:25.800 --> 18:28.840
Your dad's not here.
I lied to you.

18:28.880 --> 18:30.600
There wasn't an accident.

18:30.640 --> 18:32.080
VANDA:
You're sick.

18:32.120 --> 18:34.040
You know that, hey?

18:34.080 --> 18:35.320
Come.

18:36.640 --> 18:38.320
How long did it take you
to get here?

18:38.360 --> 18:41.760
15 minutes? 15 minutes
living with that uncertainty.

18:41.800 --> 18:43.120
Now maybe you understand
that feeling.

18:43.160 --> 18:44.520
That sick feeling
in your stomach.

18:44.560 --> 18:45.760
That's what I've been feeling

18:45.800 --> 18:47.320
ever since I saw that
photograph.

18:47.360 --> 18:48.520
So, you take my daughter,

18:48.560 --> 18:49.640
and now you ask me
to help you?

18:49.680 --> 18:51.000
What is wrong with you?

18:51.040 --> 18:53.760
Your ex, Pieter, he's
the only one who can help me.

18:53.800 --> 18:55.280
He's the only one
who can tell me for sure

18:55.320 --> 18:56.560
if my husband's alive or not.

18:56.600 --> 18:58.400
Why are you protecting him?

18:58.440 --> 19:02.000
-You don't even like him.
-Because he's trouble.

19:02.040 --> 19:03.880
And I don't want trouble
in my life.

19:03.920 --> 19:07.280
Get in the car, sweetie.

19:07.320 --> 19:09.600
Look, I'm sorry.

19:09.640 --> 19:13.040
I hope I didn't scare
your daughter.

19:13.080 --> 19:16.200
Look, please.
I don't know what to do.

19:16.240 --> 19:18.560
You're the only one
who can help me.

19:20.880 --> 19:23.240
He moves around a lot.

19:23.280 --> 19:25.480
Months go by,
I don't hear from him.

19:25.520 --> 19:28.200
But when he sent Mia's card,

19:28.240 --> 19:30.320
he called, and he said
he was going to Kisima.

19:30.360 --> 19:31.720
Thank you.

19:31.760 --> 19:33.840
And if I see you again, bitch,

19:33.880 --> 19:35.120
I'm calling the police.
All right?

19:35.160 --> 19:37.480
All right.

19:37.520 --> 19:39.560
-[car door slams shut]
-[sighs]

19:39.600 --> 19:41.680
[car starts]

20:01.160 --> 20:03.160
[indistinct shouting]

20:14.000 --> 20:16.960
It's a border check-point.
Not a guillotine.

20:17.000 --> 20:18.520
What's in the crate?

20:18.560 --> 20:20.480
Columbia's finest...

20:22.440 --> 20:23.760
...coffee beans.

20:23.800 --> 20:25.080
Stop it.

20:28.480 --> 20:30.080
Just breathe...

20:35.080 --> 20:36.320
[truck starts]

20:52.120 --> 20:53.720
Where are you doing?

20:53.760 --> 20:56.480
Rwanda. Coffee in the back.

20:56.520 --> 20:57.920
Papers, please.

21:07.080 --> 21:08.280
[man calls out in Swahili]

21:10.440 --> 21:11.440
Wait here.

21:18.680 --> 21:20.800
Why's he going round the back?

21:20.840 --> 21:22.160
Just be quiet.

21:42.080 --> 21:43.680
We're out of coffee.

21:43.720 --> 21:46.160
Think they'd notice
a handful missing?

21:47.400 --> 21:48.800
Take two.

21:48.840 --> 21:49.960
Thanks very much.

21:50.000 --> 21:51.640
So, your papers.

21:51.680 --> 21:53.320
Have a good trip.

21:53.360 --> 21:55.720
GUARD:
Bon voyage.

21:55.760 --> 21:58.680
[truck starts]

21:58.720 --> 22:00.400
We still have our heads.

22:20.640 --> 22:22.640
[music plays, patrons chatter]

22:26.520 --> 22:28.480
Interesting meeting place.

22:28.520 --> 22:30.440
I told my driver
I wanted a beer.

22:30.480 --> 22:32.880
He was very keen I come here.

22:32.920 --> 22:34.560
Is everything okay
with your wife?

22:34.600 --> 22:36.560
It will be.

22:36.600 --> 22:39.160
Her ex-husband is violent.
He won't leave us alone.

22:39.200 --> 22:41.120
He's the one
that smashed my car.

22:41.160 --> 22:43.440
It's complicated.

22:43.480 --> 22:47.240
Oh, God, Emmanuel. I'm sorry.

22:47.280 --> 22:49.240
Hopefully it's over.

22:49.280 --> 22:51.600
I'm glad you found someone.

22:51.640 --> 22:53.600
You know,
you never told me how you met.

22:53.640 --> 22:55.440
-[crowd groans]
-Oh.

22:55.480 --> 22:56.920
-[Emmanuel chuckles]
-Perfect.

22:56.960 --> 22:59.800
Only two things are certain
in Kinshasa:

22:59.840 --> 23:01.000
traffic and power cuts.

23:01.040 --> 23:02.880
Well, nobody seems to mind.

23:02.920 --> 23:05.280
60 years ago, we had trains,

23:05.320 --> 23:08.600
roads, steamboats
up and down the Congo River

23:08.640 --> 23:10.080
full of white people

23:10.120 --> 23:12.760
come to discover
a world beyond their own

23:12.800 --> 23:16.040
only to return home
with their minds no broader

23:16.080 --> 23:18.800
and themselves no different
but for their suntan.

23:18.840 --> 23:21.480
We were-- what's that word

23:21.520 --> 23:23.120
we're not allowed to use--

23:23.160 --> 23:25.320
civilized.
[chuckles softly]

23:25.360 --> 23:26.880
On the surface, anyway.

23:26.920 --> 23:30.800
The truth is that things
were probably always rotten.

23:30.840 --> 23:32.640
But now...

23:32.680 --> 23:34.640
now we don't lie about it.

23:34.680 --> 23:36.120
I can never figure out

23:36.160 --> 23:38.160
whether you're an optimist
or a pessimist.

23:38.200 --> 23:39.560
I am a pragmatist.

23:41.600 --> 23:43.680
So, tell me. What did you learn?

23:43.720 --> 23:46.040
I found out where
Pieter Bello is.

23:46.080 --> 23:49.040
-Or where he will be.
-Where?

23:49.080 --> 23:51.040
Kisima.

23:51.080 --> 23:52.600
There's a flight

23:52.640 --> 23:54.160
to Goma tomorrow morning.

23:54.200 --> 23:57.280
I'll figure out how
to get to Kisima from there.

23:57.320 --> 23:59.360
Kisima is not
the most stable place.

23:59.400 --> 24:01.720
It's full of militia,
rebels, mercenaries.

24:01.760 --> 24:03.680
No, if Pieter moves on, I lose

24:03.720 --> 24:05.960
my chance to find him.

24:06.000 --> 24:07.680
You don't have to come,
Emmanuel.

24:07.720 --> 24:09.200
You've done more than enough.

24:09.240 --> 24:11.400
No, I have not.

24:14.440 --> 24:16.400
There's something
you should know.

24:16.440 --> 24:19.160
I tried to say it before.

24:19.200 --> 24:22.280
It's my fault Gaelle is gone.

24:22.320 --> 24:24.480
What do you mean?

24:24.520 --> 24:26.360
Months after Gaelle died,

24:26.400 --> 24:29.240
I finally went
to clear her possessions.

24:29.280 --> 24:31.280
♪ ♪

24:55.760 --> 24:58.840
I think she left her diary
behind for me to find

24:58.880 --> 25:02.080
in case she did not return.

25:03.080 --> 25:05.080
What did it say?

25:11.640 --> 25:12.600
EMMANUEL [over phone]:
Allo?

25:12.640 --> 25:13.640
Hello my love.

25:15.200 --> 25:16.600
I'm sorry. You sound busy.

25:16.640 --> 25:18.880
Sorry, I have a deadline.

25:18.920 --> 25:20.960
We'll speak tonight.
Have a good flight.

25:21.000 --> 25:22.160
I love you.

25:25.640 --> 25:28.000
[plane flying overhead]

25:30.000 --> 25:32.840
EMMANUEL: Everyone knew
we owed a lot of money,

25:32.880 --> 25:36.800
and then, uh, someone
came to her with an offer.

25:36.840 --> 25:38.840
I don't know who.

25:40.840 --> 25:42.120
That's what we talked about?

25:54.680 --> 25:57.440
No one will look twice
at someone like you, okay?

25:57.480 --> 25:59.440
Hey!

26:04.640 --> 26:06.720
For you...

26:09.400 --> 26:12.360
The other half will be paid
when you land in Kinshasa.

26:20.840 --> 26:22.840
♪ ♪

26:39.960 --> 26:41.920
EMMANUEL:
I was a gambler.

26:41.960 --> 26:43.480
It was my fault
we were in debt.

26:43.520 --> 26:45.920
So she agreed

26:45.960 --> 26:47.640
to take something
on that flight.

26:47.680 --> 26:49.960
Drugs, information...

26:50.000 --> 26:52.120
I don't know.

26:52.160 --> 26:55.720
And Gaelle died trying
to make up for my mistakes.

26:55.760 --> 26:58.040
No matter how dangerous
it might be,

26:58.080 --> 27:00.800
I owe it to her
to find the truth.

27:00.840 --> 27:02.800
Maybe then her...

27:02.840 --> 27:06.000
her soul can find
some kind of peace.

27:24.320 --> 27:26.320
[insects trilling]

27:52.240 --> 27:54.240
♪ ♪

28:17.200 --> 28:19.200
♪ ♪

28:29.160 --> 28:32.760
You don't have to go, Emmanuel.

28:32.800 --> 28:36.440
First Violet, then Will...

28:36.480 --> 28:38.680
Georgia needs me.

28:40.840 --> 28:43.360
I was lucky. I met you.

28:53.040 --> 28:56.400
There was a tomorrow
for my story.

29:00.880 --> 29:03.000
♪ ♪

29:18.440 --> 29:20.840
Just promise
you'll be back soon.

29:26.640 --> 29:28.600
Chérie.

29:51.080 --> 29:52.680
JUDITH:
Morning.

29:52.720 --> 29:54.840
-Hi.
-You were out late last night.

29:54.880 --> 29:57.400
I waited up, but, uh...

29:57.440 --> 29:58.800
Yeah, Emmanuel and I
went for a drink.

29:58.840 --> 30:01.200
Thanks.

30:02.200 --> 30:05.080
So, how's it going?

30:05.120 --> 30:07.440
Pieter Bello's in Kisima.
I've got a flight

30:07.480 --> 30:09.000
to Goma in a couple of hours.

30:09.040 --> 30:10.880
Okay.

30:10.920 --> 30:12.520
You know, Kisima's
not the easiest place

30:12.560 --> 30:14.360
-to get to.
-Yeah, I've heard.

30:14.400 --> 30:16.120
We have an office
in that region.

30:16.160 --> 30:18.040
And take it from me,
you don't want to rush there.

30:18.080 --> 30:19.280
All I've done is wait.

30:19.320 --> 30:21.640
Wait for things to be different,
wait for tomorrow,

30:21.680 --> 30:23.480
wait for the next day.
I'm sick of it.

30:26.080 --> 30:29.240
This man, um, Pieter?

30:29.280 --> 30:31.320
[scoffs]

30:31.360 --> 30:32.760
What could he possibly want

30:32.800 --> 30:34.680
-with Will?
-I have no idea.

30:34.720 --> 30:36.960
I keep asking myself,
was Will different?

30:37.000 --> 30:39.440
Was he distracted?

30:39.480 --> 30:40.840
He wasn't.

30:40.880 --> 30:42.320
Right up until
he took that plane,

30:42.360 --> 30:44.000
when I spoke to him, he was...

30:44.040 --> 30:45.760
he was Will.

30:45.800 --> 30:48.320
If he is still alive...

30:48.360 --> 30:50.320
then what the hell happened?

30:50.360 --> 30:54.000
That's what I want to ask
Pieter Bello.

30:55.000 --> 30:57.000
[birds singing]

31:03.000 --> 31:05.000
[sound of rooster crowing]

31:09.560 --> 31:11.560
[crowing stops]

31:38.000 --> 31:39.960
[chuckles]:
Today's the day.

31:40.000 --> 31:42.400
Strange, isn't it?

31:42.440 --> 31:46.920
I'm just waiting here
like it's any other morning.

31:46.960 --> 31:50.520
But inside I feel
like Francois Pienaar

31:50.560 --> 31:51.840
at Ellis Park.

31:51.880 --> 31:53.320
Ready to make history.

31:53.360 --> 31:55.320
Does that make me
Nelson Mandela?

31:55.360 --> 31:57.280
[Pieter laughs]

32:00.320 --> 32:02.320
-Let's get started.
-Mm.

32:08.920 --> 32:10.880
GEORGIA:
Are you sure about this?

32:10.920 --> 32:13.760
I am.
You don't tie a bundle of wood

32:13.800 --> 32:15.080
-with one hand.
-[chuckles]

32:15.120 --> 32:17.560
[phone ringing]

32:17.600 --> 32:20.000
-Oh, excuse me. Hold on.
-Yeah.

32:20.040 --> 32:22.640
Yes, my love.

32:22.680 --> 32:23.880
Slow down, slow down,
what is it?

32:23.920 --> 32:25.000
-That's Ivette?
-Oui.

32:25.040 --> 32:26.880
Where is he now?

32:26.920 --> 32:28.560
-Okay.
-Emmanuel. Go see her.
Make sure she's okay.

32:28.600 --> 32:30.080
What about the flight?

32:30.120 --> 32:31.880
Well, this is much more
important. I'll get a taxi.

32:31.920 --> 32:33.600
You go. Take the car. Go.

32:33.640 --> 32:35.480
-Thank you, Georgia. I'm sorry.
-Yeah.

32:35.520 --> 32:37.240
[speaking French]

32:38.240 --> 32:39.520
Bye.

32:46.000 --> 32:48.000
[engine sputters]

32:54.720 --> 32:57.440
-[grunts]
-Georgia, get back!

32:57.480 --> 33:00.240
-Get back!
-[screaming]

33:00.280 --> 33:01.640
Georgia!

33:01.680 --> 33:04.680
Georgia! Get back!

33:04.720 --> 33:07.000
[Georgia screaming]

33:16.840 --> 33:18.840
[Judith speaking
in French nearby]

33:22.520 --> 33:24.520
[indistinct conversation]

33:46.080 --> 33:48.520
Right, we can go.

33:50.440 --> 33:52.560
Georgia?

33:54.680 --> 33:58.080
You think the world's done
everything it can do...

34:02.160 --> 34:04.880
When does it stop?

34:08.640 --> 34:12.480
Why would anybody want
to do this to you?

34:12.520 --> 34:14.520
I don't know.

34:16.160 --> 34:19.360
None of this makes any sense.

34:25.200 --> 34:28.040
You didn't tell the police
about Will.

34:28.080 --> 34:29.520
When I mentioned his name,

34:29.560 --> 34:31.640
it was the first time
they'd heard of it.

34:31.680 --> 34:33.640
Someone sent you that note.

34:33.680 --> 34:35.600
They told you to go home
and when you didn't...

34:35.640 --> 34:38.360
It's my fault.
[inhales]

34:38.400 --> 34:41.440
It's my fault he's dead.

34:49.400 --> 34:51.880
[sobbing]

34:56.640 --> 34:58.640
♪ ♪

35:06.800 --> 35:08.800
[siren wails in distance]

35:17.080 --> 35:18.840
I'll wait in the car.

35:18.880 --> 35:20.520
-Thank you.
-Beatrix?

35:20.560 --> 35:21.680
Ariel.

35:21.720 --> 35:22.920
I'm glad you came.

35:22.960 --> 35:24.200
I was starting to worry.

35:24.240 --> 35:27.240
You kind of disappeared
the last two days.

35:27.280 --> 35:29.600
We don't know each other.

35:29.640 --> 35:31.000
Okay.

35:31.040 --> 35:33.160
So it's none of my business,
is it?

35:33.200 --> 35:34.560
What you have and haven't done.

35:34.600 --> 35:37.280
The things
that came before we met.

35:37.320 --> 35:39.800
What is it you want to ask me,
Beatrix?

35:39.840 --> 35:43.080
Sankuru Airways Flight 19.

35:43.120 --> 35:47.520
There was a survivor,
Dominique Mutombo.

35:47.560 --> 35:50.840
She died two days later
from her injuries.

35:50.880 --> 35:53.440
There was no mention of you.

35:58.080 --> 36:00.040
Why did you lie?

36:00.080 --> 36:02.360
Wh-- Is this some sort of story

36:02.400 --> 36:04.560
that you tell women
to get them into bed?

36:04.600 --> 36:06.240
[Ariel scoffs]

36:06.280 --> 36:08.520
What?

36:08.560 --> 36:11.120
Tell me. You owe me that.

36:11.160 --> 36:13.680
I-I owe you nothing.

36:14.960 --> 36:17.920
What kind of a person are you?

36:17.960 --> 36:20.040
What kind of a person would lie
about a thing like...

36:20.080 --> 36:21.240
You know what?

36:21.280 --> 36:24.080
You're right.

36:24.120 --> 36:26.440
You know nothing about me.

36:26.480 --> 36:28.520
You're absolutely right
about that.

36:28.560 --> 36:31.200
You don't know anything
about me.

36:37.760 --> 36:40.320
WAITER:
Sir, let me help you.

36:40.360 --> 36:42.360
ARIEL:
Thank you.

36:46.160 --> 36:48.160
♪ ♪

36:50.080 --> 36:52.080
[birds chirping]

36:57.840 --> 36:59.840
♪ ♪

37:07.840 --> 37:09.680
[knocking on door]

37:12.440 --> 37:15.200
Hello.

37:15.240 --> 37:18.320
What are you doing here?

37:18.360 --> 37:20.720
I... came to say I'm sorry.

37:20.760 --> 37:23.600
Sorry.

37:23.640 --> 37:26.440
How dare you?

37:26.480 --> 37:29.560
How dare you?

37:29.600 --> 37:32.680
Hasn't there been enough misery?

37:32.720 --> 37:36.880
Haven't we all lost enough?

37:36.920 --> 37:39.480
When Emmanuel told me why
you were here,

37:39.520 --> 37:42.480
what you wanted from him,

37:42.520 --> 37:47.200
it was me
who felt sorry for you.

37:47.240 --> 37:49.600
A sad woman
who could not let go.

37:52.400 --> 37:56.560
But nor could he.

37:56.600 --> 37:59.480
He said it was for you.

37:59.520 --> 38:01.480
He said he owed you,
but I knew.

38:01.520 --> 38:05.360
I knew it was for her.

38:05.400 --> 38:10.200
I do not mind that he loved her
still-- Gaelle.

38:10.240 --> 38:12.680
I knew that before we married.

38:12.720 --> 38:16.040
But he was trying to move on

38:16.080 --> 38:18.160
into our new life.

38:18.200 --> 38:20.320
Past all the sadness.

38:20.360 --> 38:22.360
And then you came along.

38:22.400 --> 38:24.520
I should never have asked him
to help me.

38:24.560 --> 38:26.520
-I...
-But you did.

38:26.560 --> 38:28.480
And now...

38:31.960 --> 38:35.640
[crying]:
Now I cannot say anything.

38:37.880 --> 38:41.280
Now I cannot even
kiss him good night.

38:43.840 --> 38:45.400
Tell him his shirt is untucked

38:45.440 --> 38:47.480
every morning before
he goes to work.

38:49.480 --> 38:51.320
Whoever did this,
I promise you,

38:51.360 --> 38:53.080
I will find them;
I promise you.

38:53.120 --> 38:56.080
The only promise you need
to make is to Emmanuel.

38:56.120 --> 39:00.920
He is dead because of you.

39:00.960 --> 39:03.720
Go on then.

39:03.760 --> 39:05.720
You find his murderer.

39:05.760 --> 39:08.760
And if you know
what is good for you,

39:08.800 --> 39:11.360
you stay away from me.

39:14.960 --> 39:16.960
[sobbing]

39:18.720 --> 39:20.680
[exhales]

39:20.720 --> 39:22.680
[Ivette continues sobbing]

39:34.800 --> 39:37.800
JUDITH:
That can't have been easy.

39:37.840 --> 39:39.760
I need to find Pieter Bello.

39:39.800 --> 39:42.120
[inhales and exhales sharply]

39:42.160 --> 39:44.520
Yeah. Courage and stupidity

39:44.560 --> 39:46.800
are often confused
with each other.

39:46.840 --> 39:48.520
I didn't actually ask
your opinion.

39:48.560 --> 39:50.920
Hey, listen, somebody just
tried to have you killed.

39:50.960 --> 39:53.240
The only thing you should be
doing is going back home.

39:53.280 --> 39:55.600
Getting as far away from
this place as you can.

39:55.640 --> 39:57.840
I have to find out why Bello
lied to me about who he is,

39:57.880 --> 39:59.880
and what he was doing
with my husband in Kinshasa.

39:59.920 --> 40:01.040
You think he'll just tell you?

40:01.080 --> 40:02.800
I have to try.

40:12.800 --> 40:15.120
If you approach him
somewhere public.

40:15.160 --> 40:17.240
It's not like you're a threat
to him, right?

40:17.280 --> 40:19.040
You just want to know
about Will.

40:19.080 --> 40:21.440
The question is getting there.

40:21.480 --> 40:23.840
Things in the East aren't
exactly stable right now.

40:23.880 --> 40:26.000
It's not like I'm safe here,
is it?

40:26.040 --> 40:27.840
We need to find someone
who knows the area.

40:27.880 --> 40:30.200
We?

40:30.240 --> 40:32.640
A man died in front of my home;
I want to know why.

40:32.680 --> 40:34.800
You said it was too dangerous.

40:34.840 --> 40:36.080
Yeah, it is.

40:36.120 --> 40:37.400
My office in Goma,

40:37.440 --> 40:38.560
I'm due a visit there anyway.

40:38.600 --> 40:39.560
When I get there,

40:39.600 --> 40:40.920
I'll find someone reliable

40:40.960 --> 40:42.120
to take you into the bush.

40:42.160 --> 40:44.960
They can get you to Kisima,
safely.

40:46.160 --> 40:47.560
Okay.

40:47.600 --> 40:49.880
We can leave first thing
tomorrow.

40:49.920 --> 40:52.880
Thank you.

40:52.920 --> 40:55.200
You thought I was mad,
didn't you?

40:55.240 --> 40:56.640
In a mad world,

40:56.680 --> 41:00.120
only the mad are sane,
aren't they?

41:04.760 --> 41:06.760
[sighs]

41:15.680 --> 41:17.680
[playing piano]

41:28.520 --> 41:30.520
[continues playing]

41:41.560 --> 41:43.560
[doorbell rings]

41:50.760 --> 41:52.720
[intercom beeps,
door lock buzzes]

41:52.760 --> 41:55.360
BEATRIX:
There's a sofa here.

42:01.480 --> 42:03.520
[sighs]

42:05.520 --> 42:08.680
I came to say I'm sorry.

42:08.720 --> 42:11.600
And even though we don't exactly
know each other that well...

42:11.640 --> 42:13.840
What do you want, Ariel?

42:15.600 --> 42:18.680
To apologize, to explain.

42:21.320 --> 42:23.080
Right.

42:23.120 --> 42:26.000
I never told anyone
about that plane crash.

42:26.040 --> 42:27.440
Not a soul.

42:27.480 --> 42:29.120
Why not?

42:30.560 --> 42:33.880
I'm scared.

42:33.920 --> 42:36.280
Because, Beatrix,
nothing you will ever hear

42:36.320 --> 42:40.440
about that place crash is true.

42:40.480 --> 42:42.680
I was on that plane
when it went down,

42:42.720 --> 42:46.240
but it wasn't how
they reported it.

42:46.280 --> 42:47.880
It wasn't mechanical failure.

42:47.920 --> 42:49.680
There was a...

42:51.920 --> 42:53.840
There was a bomb on the plane.

42:53.880 --> 42:56.120
What?

42:56.160 --> 42:59.120
I saw the person
that carried it on board.

42:59.160 --> 43:01.720
It was a woman.

43:01.760 --> 43:04.720
It was a pregnant woman.

43:04.760 --> 43:06.760
She was carrying
a black rucksack

43:06.800 --> 43:09.600
with a picture of a bright green
lion on the front.

43:09.640 --> 43:13.080
[inhales and exhales deeply]

43:13.120 --> 43:16.200
I remember it all.

43:35.720 --> 43:37.000
Long journey, right?

43:37.040 --> 43:38.000
Yes.

43:38.040 --> 43:40.320
You been to Rwanda before?

43:40.360 --> 43:42.360
I know a good bar
you should try.

43:43.640 --> 43:44.800
And this one?

43:44.840 --> 43:46.480
Don't worry about that one.

43:46.520 --> 43:49.240
I said...

43:49.280 --> 43:50.480
...you can go.

